-------------------------------
           ABOUT
-------------------------------
'Rite Editor' is a minimal text editor which runs on Linux. 
It is implemented using Gtk+2.0 and C programming language.
Rite Editor is an OPEN SOURCE Software. You can add custom external plugins to the editor to add new funtionalities.
On the whole, it is the 'rite' editor for you!


-------------------------------
           FEATURES
-------------------------------
1.  Save, Open and create a new file.
2.  Change font and search for occurrence of a string
3.  Cut, Copy, Paste and Undo text
4.  Display of line number and column number in status bar
5.  Custom Icon of the editor
6.  Add External Custom Plugins to give new funtionalities making the software open source
7.  Submit Bug Reports/ Feedbacks 
8.  Licensed under GNU GPLv3 License

-------------------------------
          REQUIREMENT
-------------------------------
1. libgtk2.0-dev ( $ sudo apt-get install build-essential libgtk2.0-dev )
2. gcc compiler

-------------------------------
         COMMAND TO RUN
-------------------------------

Compile :
---------
$ gcc editor.c -o program `pkg-config --libs --cflags gtk+-2.0`

OR

$ make

Execute :
---------
$./program

